# Environment and credential files
# NOTE: .env files MUST be included in the repo for deployment to work.
# They are auto-populated at deploy time with production MONGO_URL, API keys etc.
# Keeping them in git is safe because secrets are managed by the platform.
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
.credentials

# Environment and credential files
# IMPORTANT: do NOT add `.env` / `.env.*` / `*.env` patterns here — those
# files are required to ship with the repo so the platform can inject prod
# values at deploy time. The pytest sanity-check `test_gitignore_sanity.py`
# guards against accidental re-adds.
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
.credentials

# Environment and credential files
# IMPORTANT: do NOT add `.env` / `.env.*` / `*.env` patterns here.
# .env files MUST ship with the repo so the platform can inject prod values
# at deploy time. The pytest sanity-check guards against accidental re-adds.
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
.credentials

